A ministerial meeting of African lumber producers will convene in Cabinda, Angola to address new policies for imports and exports.
Specialists will gather on April 27 to prepare for the May 2-5 meeting, focusing on protecting tropical rainforest varieties.
The 17th Africa Timber Conference in Cabinda aims to discuss timber industry development and conservation.
Angola's Deputy Minister of Agriculture highlighted the importance of rainforest preservation.
Meanwhile, efforts in China's Xishuangbanna reserve to expand protection for rare plants and animals demonstrate a commitment to environmental conservation and sustainability.
